'''"Juke Box Music"''' is a track from [[The Kinks]]' 1977 album, [[Sleepwalker (The Kinks album)|Sleepwalker]]. It was one of the first tracks recorded in The Kinks' Konk recording complex. The song was also performed for [[Whistle Test]] in 1977.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vzjoqpTqSR4 |title=The Kinks - Juke Box Music |publisher=YouTube |date=2008-11-19 |accessdate=2014-06-13}}</ref>

==About==
"Juke Box Music" is about a music fan who believes in the lyrics of the songs that she plays repeatedly on the juke box. [[Rolling Stone]] says that the topic "should be a pathetic song, yet Davies has us tapping our feet, singing along."<ref name="archive1">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/thekinks/albums/album/174388/review/5946447/sleepwalker |title=The Kinks: Sleepwalker : Music Reviews : Rolling Stone |publisher=Web.archive.org |date=1977-04-21 |accessdate=2014-06-13 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071130023021/http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/thekinks/albums/album/174388/review/5946447/sleepwalker |archivedate=30 November 2007 }}</ref> The song was released as the second single from [[Sleepwalker (The Kinks album)|Sleepwalker]], backed with "Sleepless Night" in the U.K. and Germany (and with "Life Goes On" in the U.S.). It did not chart. "Juke Box Music" also appeared on ''[[Come Dancing with The Kinks]]''.

"Juke Box Music" has been positively reviewed by many critics. [[Robert Christgau]] recommended the track in his review of the [[Sleepwalker (The Kinks album)|Sleepwalker]] album,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?id=1464 |title=CG: Artist 1464 |publisher=Robert Christgau |date= |accessdate=2014-06-13}}</ref> and ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' claimed that it "is the best song [on Sleepwalker]."<ref name="archive1"/> [[AllMusic]] called the track "exceptional",<ref>{{cite web|author=[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/sleepwalker-mw0000200593 |title=Sleepwalker - The Kinks &#124; Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date=1976-07-01 |accessdate=2014-06-13}}</ref> and said it was "yet another impressionistic portrait by the Kinks' Ray Davies".<ref>{{cite web|author=Denise Sullivan |url=http://www.allmusic.com/song/juke-box-music-mt0011382141 |title=Juke Box Music - The Kinks &#124; Listen, Appearances, Song Review |publisher=AllMusic |date=2006-10-17 |accessdate=2014-06-13}}</ref>

